{{About|the Book of Mormon figure|the Biblical site|Ammah}}
{{Religious text primary|date=October 2011}}

According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Ammah''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|æ|m|ɑː}})<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «ăm´mä»</ref> was a [[Nephite]] missionary from 1st century BC, and a companion to [[Aaron (Nephite)|Aaron]]. Ammah was part of the missionary delegation to the [[Lamanites]]<ref>[http://scriptures.lds.org/en/alma/21/11#11 Alma 21:11]</ref> that eventually led to the conversion of the [[Ammonites (Book of Mormon)|Ammonites]]. He was imprisoned with Aaron during his ministry.<ref>[http://scriptures.lds.org/en/alma/20/2#2 Alma 20:2]</ref>

